                           saints; name of the scribe; names of the donors; incipit of Text I and
                           III, and its subsections (fols. 4ra, 6vb, 11vb, 24va, 37ra, 41va, 42vb,
                           43ra, 50rb, 52vb, 60vb, 64rb, 67va, 71va, 75ra, 76vb, 77rb, 78va, 80rb,
                           81ra); incipit of Text II; incipit of Text IV; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the quire
                           marks.
 In the incipit page of Texts I, III and IV (fols. 4r, 11vb,
                           87ra), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines)</seg>
